```

## File Descriptions

### Core Files
- main.py: FastAPI application initialization, middleware setup, route inclusion
- config.py: Environment variables, database settings, JWT configuration

### Models
- user.py: SQLAlchemy User model with fields (id, name, email, password, role)
- task.py: SQLAlchemy Task model with fields (id, title, description, status, priority, dueDate, createdBy, assignedTo)

### Schemas (Pydantic)
- user.py: UserCreate, UserLogin, UserResponse, UserUpdate
- task.py: TaskCreate, TaskUpdate, TaskResponse, TaskFilter
- auth.py: Token, TokenData, RefreshToken

### Routes
- auth.py: `/api/v1/auth/*` - registration, login, logout, refresh, profile
- tasks.py: `/api/v1/tasks/*` - CRUD operations, filtering, statistics
- admin.py: `/api/v1/admin/*` - user management, role updates

### Middleware
- auth.py: JWT token verification, user extraction
- authorization.py: Role-based permission checking
- rate_limit.py: IP-based request limiting (100 req/15 min)

### Services
- Business logic layer separating concerns from routes
- Handles database operations, validations, and complex operations

### Utils
- security.py: bcrypt password hashing, JWT token generation/verification
- validators.py: Email format, password strength validation

## Technology Stack
- Framework: FastAPI 0.104+
- Database: PostgreSQL with SQLAlchemy ORM
- Authentication: JWT (PyJWT)
- Password: bcrypt
- Validation: Pydantic v2
- Rate Limiting: slowapi
- Testing: pytest
